---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

import { PAGE_METADATA } from '~/utils/metadata';
---

<Layout metadata={PAGE_METADATA.faq}>
  <section class="py-12">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center text-takai-blue">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="text-center text-lg text-gray-700">
        Get clear answers about TAKAI's Japanese paint protection and heat-control films — how they work, how to maintain them, and why thousands of car owners trust TAKAI to protect their vehicles.
      </p>

      <!-- FAQ Items -->
      <div class="divide-y divide-takai-gold/40">
        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">Why choose TAKAI over other protection films?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            TAKAI films are developed and manufactured in Japan under strict automotive standards. Every layer — from adhesive to top-coat — is engineered for clarity, UV resistance, and long-term durability. The result: perfect protection without altering your car's color, sensors, or warranty.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">How long does TAKAI film last?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            TAKAI Premium films come with a <strong>10-year warranty</strong>, while TAKAI Premium Plus carries a <strong>15-year warranty</strong>. These warranties cover yellowing, cracking, bubbling, and peeling — ensuring your investment remains visually flawless.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">Does installation require removing car parts?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            No. TAKAI films are designed for <strong>precision fit without disassembly</strong>. Our advanced templates and edge-wrapping techniques keep factory sensors, trims, and seals intact — preserving both aesthetics and manufacturer warranty.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">Can the film repair itself from scratches?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. Minor swirls and micro-scratches <strong>self-heal under sunlight or gentle heat</strong>, thanks to TAKAI's nanotechnology-infused top-coat. Your car maintains a fresh, high-gloss finish year after year.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">What's the difference between TAKAI Premium and TAKAI Premium Plus?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>TAKAI Premium:</strong> Ideal for daily-driven vehicles seeking gloss and impact resistance.<br/>
            <strong>TAKAI Premium Plus:</strong> A next-generation film designed for <strong>electric and high-performance cars</strong>, offering superior heat rejection and enhanced elasticity for complex curves.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">How should I care for the film after installation?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You can wash your car normally after 7 days. Use neutral pH car shampoo and soft microfiber towels. Avoid harsh chemicals or automatic brushes. TAKAI films are compatible with ceramic coatings for added ease of maintenance.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">Can TAKAI film be removed or replaced later?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Yes — professional installers can remove it without leaving residue or damaging the paint. This makes it ideal for leased vehicles or resale preparation.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="py-6 group">
          <summary class="text-xl font-semibold text-takai-blue cursor-pointer hover:text-takai-gold">Where can I install TAKAI products?</summary>
          <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            TAKAI films are installed exclusively by <strong>authorized partners</strong> trained to Japanese standards. Visit the "Find Installer" section to locate your nearest certified workshop.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
